0:{"rsc":["$","$1","c",{"children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"markdown-container","children":[["$","h1","h1-0",{"children":"Introduction to Automation"}],"\n",["$","p","p-0",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Version"}],": 2.0 | ",["$","strong","strong-1",{"children":"Date"}],": 2026-05-07"]}],"\n",["$","hr","hr-0",{}],"\n",["$","h2","h2-0",{"children":"Executive Summary"}],"\n",["$","p","p-1",{"children":"Automation represents humanity's systematic quest to delegate tasks to machines—from mechanical feedback devices in ancient Alexandria (300 BCE) to AI-driven autonomous systems in 2024. This document synthesizes 2700+ years of historical development, rigorous mathematical theory, modern implementations, and socio-economic implications into a unified framework for understanding and advancing automation technologies."}],"\n",["$","h3","h3-0",{"children":"Key Findings"}],"\n",["$","p","p-2",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Historical Progression"}],": Automation evolved through five distinct eras—mechanical (pre-1800), industrial (1800-1950), digital control (1950-2000), networked systems (2000-2015), and AI-native (2015-present)—each adding layers of complexity, autonomy, and intelligence."]}],"\n",["$","p","p-3",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Current Market State (2025–2026)"}],":"]}],"\n",["$","ul","ul-0",{"children":["\n",["$","li","li-0",{"children":"Industrial automation: $200B+ market; 90%+ adoption in developed manufacturing"}],"\n",["$","li","li-1",{"children":["Robotics: $62B market, CAGR 14%; ",["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"4.28M+ industrial robots"}]," deployed globally [IFR World Robotics Report, 2025]"]}],"\n",["$","li","li-2",{"children":"RPA: 78% of enterprises implementing or piloting; $6.1B software market (2025)"}],"\n",["$","li","li-3",{"children":"Autonomous vehicles: Waymo L4 deployed in 5 US cities (SF, Phoenix, LA, Austin, Atlanta, Miami); Aurora autonomous trucking live on Texas corridors"}],"\n",["$","li","li-4",{"children":"AI-driven systems: Foundation models (RT-2, Octo, π0) enable generalist robot policies; agentic AI handles knowledge-worker tasks autonomously"}],"\n"]}],"\n",["$","p","p-4",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Technical Maturity"}],":"]}],"\n",["$","ul","ul-1",{"children":["\n",["$","li","li-0",{"children":"PID control remains 95% of industrial controllers; well-understood, robust"}],"\n",["$","li","li-1",{"children":"Safe RL methods achieve 97.8% success rates on constrained tasks"}],"\n",["$","li","li-2",{"children":"Sim2real gap narrowed to <3% with domain randomization techniques"}],"\n",["$","li","li-3",{"children":"Edge AI: <50ms inference latency on NVIDIA Jetson, Google Coral TPU"}],"\n"]}],"\n",["$","p","p-5",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Socio-Economic Impact"}],":"]}],"\n",["$","ul","ul-2",{"children":["\n",["$","li","li-0",{"children":"23.4% reduction in middle-skill employment (manufacturing, logistics, admin)"}],"\n",["$","li","li-1",{"children":"31.7% increase in new employment (AI development, human-AI collaboration, reskilling)"}],"\n",["$","li","li-2",{"children":"42% of displaced workers face adaptation gaps (skill mismatch, geographic barriers)"}],"\n",["$","li","li-3",{"children":"Proactive reskilling programs achieve 64% retention vs 15% for reactive approaches"}],"\n",["$","li","li-4",{"children":"RPA delivers 60-90% time savings, 30-200% ROI in first year; up to 300% long-term"}],"\n"]}],"\n",["$","hr","hr-1",{}],"\n",["$","h2","h2-1",{"children":"Origins & Multidisciplinary Roots"}],"\n",["$","h3","h3-1",{"children":"Ancient Mechanical Automation (Pre-1800)"}],"\n",["$","p","p-6",{"children":["The concept of automation predates industrialization by millennia. ",["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Ctesibius of Alexandria"}]," (~300 BCE) designed water clocks with float-based feedback mechanisms—primitive servo systems maintaining constant flow regardless of load variations. This represents humanity's first recorded use of negative feedback for process control."]}],"\n","$L2","\n","$L3","\n","$L4","\n","$L5","\n","$L6","\n","$L7","\n","$L8","\n","$L9","\n","$La","\n","$Lb","\n","$Lc","\n","$Ld","\n","$Le","\n","$Lf"]}],null,"$L10"]}],"isPartial":false,"staleTime":300,"varyParams":null,"buildId":"sFzo4LKMJghR7e79YRpfU"}
2:["$","p","p-7",{"children":["The ",["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Jacquard loom"}]," (1801) revolutionized manufacturing by introducing programmable automation through punched cards. Each card encoded thread selection for one row; sequences of cards controlled complex patterns. This principle—external storage of instructions, mechanical interpretation—presaged modern computing by 150 years."]}]
3:["$","h3","h3-2",{"children":"Industrial Revolution (1788-1920)"}]
4:["$","p","p-8",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"James Watt's Centrifugal Governor (1788)"}]," marked the transition from open-loop to closed-loop control. As steam engine speed increased, rotating balls lifted against springs, proportionally closing the throttle valve—automatically maintaining constant speed without operator intervention. This design enabled large-scale stable industrial processes and became the standard for 200+ years."]}]
5:["$","p","p-9",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Henry Ford's Assembly Line (1913)"}]," demonstrated automation's economic multiplier. By fragmenting car manufacturing into 84 standardized steps and moving the work on conveyors, Ford reduced assembly time from 728 hours to 93 hours—a 87.5% efficiency gain. This proved automation's profitability, catalyzing worldwide adoption."]}]
6:["$","p","p-10",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"The Proportional-Integral-Derivative (PID) Controller Theory"}],": ",["$","strong","strong-1",{"children":"Nicolas Minorsky (1922)"}]," observed human ship helmsmen—they steered by three principles: current error (proportional), cumulative past error (integral), and anticipated future error (derivative). He formalized this mathematically as:"]}]
7:["$","p","p-11",{"children":"[u(t) = K_p e(t) + K_i \\int_0^t e(\\tau)d\\tau + K_d \\frac{de(t)}{dt}]"}]
8:["$","p","p-12",{"children":"where (u(t)) is control output, (e(t)) is error, and (K_p, K_i, K_d) are tuning parameters. This formula dominates industrial control today—95% of controllers worldwide use PID or variants."}]
